comments: Harris (BKN) and Kennard (DET) engage and disengage off-ball without affecting the other's FOM.
Snell (DET) makes marginal contact with Irving's (BKN) upper half and does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Jordan (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Kennard's (DET) path after the hand-off and does not deliver the contact.
Kennard (DET) makes marginal contact with Harris' (BKN) lower body and doesn't affect his SQBR or ability to get into his natural shooting motion.
Kennard (DET) makes incidental contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) backside as he moves through the lane.
Harris (BKN) makes marginal contact with Kennard (DET) that doesn't affect his SQBR as he is able to move through it.
Drummond (DET) establishes himself in a screening position in Harris' (BKN) path and absorbs the contact as it is made.
Kennard (DET) makes marginal contact with his off-arm to Harris' (BKN) front as he releases from the engagement and steps back toward the free throw line.
After Prince (BKN) and Morris (DET) initially engage following the release of the shot attempt, Prince extends his left arm into Morris' chest and dislodges him from his legally obtained position.
Brown (DET) puts a marginal hand to Irving's (BKN) side after his release and the contact doesn't affect his ability to follow-through naturally.
Morris (BKN) back-taps the ball, which does not subsequently make contact with the baseline.
Jordan (BKN) makes marginal contact with Drummond's (DET) backside during rebounding.
Brown (DET) makes incidental contact with Irving (BKN) as they both legally go for the loose ball.
Jordan (BKN) cleanly dislodges the ball prior to the marginal body contact during Brown's (DET) driving shot attempt.
Drummond (DET) extends his arms into Irving's (BKN) backside and dislodges him during the rebound. The contact precedes, and subsequently causes, any potential traveling violation by Irving.
Harris (BKN) makes marginal contact with Kennard (DET) and doesn't affect his FOM during the inbound.
Harris (BKN) makes marginal body contact with Kennard (DET) after the release of his shot attempt and does not affect his ability to follow-through naturally.
Morris (DET) briefly has his right hand on Prince's (BKN) opposite side hip, but slides it off without affecting his FOM.
Jordan (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in Brown's (DET) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Drummond (DET) maintains legal guarding position as Irving (BKN) initiates contact during his driving shot attempt.
Harris (BKN) makes marginal body contact with Kennard (DET) that does not affect his SQBR in the backcourt.

Morris (DET) re-establishes his right foot in the back-court before making contact with the ball. Morris then passes the ball to Kennard in the front-court within eight seconds of the possession's origin.
Dinwiddie (BKN) delivers some contact to Brown (DET) as he sets the screen, but it is marginal and does not affect Brown's ability to defend. The two then briefly engage and disengage.
Harris (BKN) commits the take foul on Kennard (DET).
Brown (DET) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (BKN).
Jordan (BKN) commits the take foul on Drummond (DET).
Prince (BKN) firms up in his screening position in Galloway's (DET) path and does not deliver the contact.
Galloway (DET) commits the take foul on Prince (BKN).
Allen (BKN) and Morris (DET) each engage with one another during rebounding, but do not affect the other's ability to retrieve the ball.
Jordan (BKN) commits a take foul on Drummond (DET).
